TY  - JOUR
AU  - Wang, Yajun
T1  - Why Can Margin Requirements Increase Volatility and Benefit Margin Constrained Investors?*
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfv041
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 20
IS  - 4
SP  - 1449
EP  - 1485
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We propose a tractable equilibrium model to examine how margin requirements affect asset prices, market volatility, and market participants’ welfare. We show that margin requirements can have opposite effects on market volatility when they constrain different investors and thus can help explain why empirical results have been mixed. Contrary to one of the main regulatory goals, we find that even though margin requirements restrict borrowing and shorting, they can significantly increase market volatility. In addition, margin requirements can make margin constrained investors better off and can lead to a greater return reversal. Our analysis also provides new empirically testable implications.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfv041
ER  - 



